
[1]idiopathic

   IDIOPATH'IC, a. [See Idiopathy.] Pertaining to idiopathy; indicating a
   disease peculiar to a particular part of the body, and not arising from
   any preceding disease; as idiopathic head-ach. The epilepsy is
   idiopathic, when it proceeds from some fault in the brain; but
   sympathetic,when it is the consequence of some other disorder.

   The term idiopathic is also applied to general as well as local
   diseases, as idiopathic fever. It then signifies, not sympathetic or
   symptomatic, not arising from any previous disease.
